# create function

my_plot <- function(ts, main = "original")
{
  par(mfrow = c(3, 1))
  plot(ts, main = main)
  
  acf(ts, main = main)
  pacf(ts, main = main)
}

check <- function(model)
  list(auto = auto.arima(model), arma = armaselect(model))
# create ts and plot it
setwd(dirname(rstudioapi::getSourceEditorContext()$path))
fu <- ts(read.csv("Furnace_temp.csv", header = T)$Furn_t)

#                         .             .                 .
# hence, this is AR(2) ~ Z_t = phi_1 * Z_{t-1} + phi_2 * Z_{t-2} + a_t,
# because ACF exp. decay and PACF cuts off after lag 2
# (phi_1 > 0, phi_2 < 0 (Wei page 44) )
# and temperature depends on previous values + random variable (AR model)
# and sarima is the best for AR(2)
# and this is the simplest model that can describe this time series
be <- ts(read.csv("Bever_Amount.csv", header = T)$Bever_amount)

# hence, this is AR(1) ~ Z_t = phi_1 * Z_{t-1} + a_t,

# and sarima is the best for AR(1)
# and this is the simplest model that can describe this time series
